<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}-{5}{y}={39}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{4}{y}=-{27}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({1},-{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+-{5}{y}={39}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}={39}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{39}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{\left(\frac{{{39}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{6}}}}\right)}+{4}{y}=-{27}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{9}}{{-{{6}}}}\cdot{\left({39}\right)}-\frac{{9}}{{-{{6}}}}{\left(-{5}\right)}{y}+{4}{y}=-{27}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{58.5}-{\left(-{7.5}\right)}{y}+{4}{y}=-{27}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7.5}{y}+{\left({4}\right)}{y}=-{27}--{58.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7.5}{y}+{\left({4}\right)}{y}={31.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{7.5}+{\left({4}\right)}\right)}{y}={31.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3.5}{y}={31.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{31.5}}{{-{{3.5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+-{5}{\left(-{9}\right)}={39}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{\left({45}\right)}={39}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}={39}-{\left({45}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}=-{6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{6}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={1}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({1},-{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

